  "texts": [
    "This increase shows itself very clearly in the illuvial hardened \"B\" layer.",
    "So, sometimes the bulk weight is 1,33-1,48 g/cm 3 at 0,6-1,0 m layer of the non-degraded and averagely degraded tea-soils before agrocultivation.",
    "As it is seen from the experiments that the porosity reduced 3,0 % in the sowing layer (0-30cm) in the averagely eroded tea soils, but the bulk mass increased 0,08 g/cm 3 compared to non-degraded soils.",
    "In 2023, the numbers that were obtained during the research indicate that a bulk weight of the podzol-gleyey-yellow soils under tea plants are slightly different from each other on sections.",
    "When the structure of fertile soils is high, there degradation process becomes very weak."
